\f1\b Xi\'92an, China
\f0\b0  \'97 one of the ancient capitals of Chinese civilization, where 
\f3\i Taoist, Buddhist, and Confucian traditions interweave
\f0\i0 . ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://pearlnewsuna.org/master-feung-the-grand-painting-and-the-art-of-being-yourself/?utm_source=chatgpt.com"}}{\fldrslt \ul \ulc2 pearlnewsuna.org}})\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
He runs a 
\f1\b cultural center in Xi\'92an
\f0\b0  (a five-floor space filled with his calligraphy and art), and he also conducts spiritual-cultural pilgrimage experiences such as visits to 
\f1\b Hua Shan
\f0\b0 , a sacred mountain with deep Taoist history. ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://pearlnewsuna.org/master-feung-the-grand-painting-and-the-art-of-being-yourself/?utm_source=chatgpt.com"}}{\fldrslt \ul \ulc2 pearlnewsuna.org}})\
